value.value: A Semantic Data Model includes study design Data Elements and the relationships between them
Dataset Descriptor does NOT include a reference to the Dataset it describes
Dataset Descriptor includes Identifying & Descriptive Dataset-Level metadata
Dataset Descriptor contains access information for the Dataset
Dataset Descriptor includes reference to related Datasets and if applicable the relevant joining Dataset Fields
Dataset Descriptor references a standard license under which the dataset can be re-used.
Dataset Descriptor includes Field-level Metadata as prescribed by a locally defined Dataset Model
Dataset Descriptor includes standard-compliant Field-level Metadata as prescribed by the adopted standard Dataset Model.
The Semantic Data Model includes a pre-defined set of Common Data Elements reported within the Datasets and the relationships between them
Dataset Descriptor includes Value-level Metadata or if applicable includes a reference to a locally defined Data Dictionary
Value Level Metadata includes Resolvable Identifiers for Controlled and/or Standard Terms reported in the Dataset
Data or metadata is hosted in non-accessible storage (e.g., personal desktop, local file system or archive)
Metadata hosting environment stores and maintains an identifiable Dataset Descriptor for each identifiable Dataset
The Data hosting environment's Persistence Model is aligned with a locally defined Domain Model to enable interpretation of Datasets
The Data hosting environment's Persistence Model is aligned with a standard Dataset model or compliant with relevant Minimum Information Reporting Guidelines
Data Hosting environment stores data in a relevant linked data store (e.g., Triple Store or Graph Databaase)
Data or metadata hosted in an accessible resource but with no retrieval capability
The Dataset and its Descriptor are indexed and retrievable (in the same or separate hosting environments) via unique and persistent identifiers
Retrieval of the Dataset and the Dataset Descriptor utilises a standardized communication protocol that is open, free and universally implementable
Metadata hosting environment provides programmatic access and retrieval (API) for the Dataset Descriptor
For each dataset, the hosting environment maintains a globally unique, persistent and resolvable identifier for access and retrieval
If applicable, Dataset hosting environment offers dataset-level authentication and authorisation capabilities
Data Hosting Environment provides semantic querying capability
Dataset's Metadata is NOT searchable via keywords or elements within the Descriptor
Metadata hosting environment offers the capability to browse and search contents of the Dataset Descriptor
Data hosting environment offers the capability to browse and search related Datasets
Data Hosting environment utilises controlled terms and/or ontology terms to search within Dataset content.
Data Hosting Environment provides semantic querying capability
